qas.question: What have Postcode 3000 and Melbourne 2030 aimed to do?
How many people did Carlton have per km2 between 2012 and 2013?
How many people did Fitzroy have per km2 between 2012 and 2013?
According to the Australian Bureau of Statistics as of June 2013, inner city Melbourne had a population density of how many people per km2?

context: After a trend of declining population density since World War II, the city has seen increased density in the inner and western suburbs, aided in part by Victorian Government planning, such as Postcode 3000 and Melbourne 2030 which have aimed to <a0_0>curtail urban sprawl<a0_0/>. According to the Australian Bureau of Statistics as of June 2013, inner city Melbourne had the highest population density with <a3_0>12,400<a3_0/> people per km2. Surrounding inner city suburbs experienced an increase in population density between 2012 and 2013; Carlton (<a1_0>9,000<a1_0/> people per km2) and Fitzroy (<a2_0>7,900<a2_0/>).
